<paragraph id="8B9898347E53FFDFFF3F76B5DBC8F923" blockId="33.[192,1441,1439,1752]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="B95344267E53FFDFFF3F76B5DE4CFA4C" bold="true" box="[192,338,1439,1463]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Definition.</emphasis>
A likely sister to 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E53FFDFFDD076B5DC61FA43" authority="Godman, [1900]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1900" box="[559,895,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Cobalopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E53FFDFFDD076B5DDADFA4C" box="[559,691,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Cobalopsis</emphasis>
Godman, [1900]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus id="549C26967E53FFDFFC6F768ADCD8FA43" box="[912,966,1440,1464]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E53FFDFFBD376B5DA82FA43" authority="Mabille, 1891" authorityName="Mabille" authorityYear="1891" box="[1068,1436,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pamphila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edda">
<emphasis id="B95344267E53FFDFFBD376B5DBF6FA4C" box="[1068,1256,1439,1463]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Pamphila edda</emphasis>
Mabille, 1891
</taxonomicName>
, which is a subjective junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E53FFDFFD5976EADB04FA23" authority="Plotz, 1882" authorityName="Plotz" authorityYear="1882" box="[678,1050,1472,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="autumna">
<emphasis id="B95344267E53FFDFFD5976EADC94FA2C" box="[678,906,1472,1495]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Hesperia autumna</emphasis>
Pl√∂tz, 1882
</taxonomicName>
) and is in a different clade from 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E53FFDFFF3F76CADEFAFA03" authority="Godman, [1901]" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1901" box="[192,484,1504,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vettius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E53FFDFFF3F76CADE08FA0C" box="[192,278,1504,1527]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Vettius</emphasis>
Godman, [1901]
</taxonomicName>
; (
<typeStatus id="549C26967E53FFDFFE0676CADD31FA03" box="[505,559,1504,1528]" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E53FFDFFD6B76F5DB0EFA03" authority="Cramer, [1777]" authorityName="Cramer" authorityYear="1777" box="[660,1040,1503,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phyllus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E53FFDFFD6B76F5DC50FA0C" box="[660,846,1503,1527]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Papilio phyllus</emphasis>
Cramer, [1777]
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="131C84B17E53FFDFFBD576CADBB0FA03" box="[1066,1198,1504,1528]" captionStart-0="Figure 11" captionStart-1="Figure 12" captionStartId-0="29.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionStartId-1="31.[192,275,1330,1352]" captionTargetBox-0="[195,1438,214,1295]" captionTargetBox-1="[194,1440,214,1295]" captionTargetId-0="figure@29.[194,1442,213,1296]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[192,1440,213,1296]" captionTargetPageId-0="29" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionText-0="Figure 11. Nuclear genome and Z chromosome trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." captionText-1="Figure 12. Mitochondrial genome and COI barcode trees of Moncina and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677257" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677259" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3677257/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3677259/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Fig. 11‚Äì12</figureCitation>
). Keys to J. 
<quantity id="4CDF35D17E53FFDFFAC876CADABEFA03" box="[1335,1440,1504,1528]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.146302" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" unit="in" value="45.13">45.13 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB6E5C57E53FFDFFF3F752ADE7DF9E3" author="Evans" box="[192,355,1536,1560]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" pagination="54 - 88" refId="ref27591" refString="Evans, W. H. 1955. A catalogue of the American Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum (Natural History). Part IV. Hesperiinae and Megathyminae. British Museum (Natural History); London. v + 499 p., pl. 54 - 88" type="book chapter" year="1955">Evans (1955)</bibRefCitation>
. Superficially indeed similar to some 
<taxonomicName id="4C27E3B77E53FFDFFCDE752ADC69F9EC" authorityName="Godman" authorityYear="1901" box="[801,887,1536,1559]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Vettius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95344267E53FFDFFCDE752ADC69F9EC" box="[801,887,1536,1559]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">Vettius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the gist of ventral wing patters, but differs from them in lacking brands in males, lacking white streak in cell 1A+2A-3A on dorsal hindwing, but having white spot in cell CuA 
<subScript id="17A39A717E53FFDFFDA37565DD7BF9A6" attach="left" box="[604,613,1615,1629]" fontSize="6" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">2</subScript>
-1A+2A on dorsal forewing and white veins on ventral hindwing. In male genitalia, uncus short and broad, arms far apart, short, gnathos not expanded in lateral view, penis narrow, curved, harpe close to ampulla, upturned, ends in a finger-like process protruding dorsad from the valva. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly423.31.1:C427T, aly423.31.1:A428C, aly2548.21.8: 
<specimenCode id="DB81304F7E53FFDFFDA475EADDB8F923" box="[603,678,1728,1752]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="33" pageNumber="32">T1491</specimenCode>
C, aly6841.51.2:A710T, aly1405.20.15:G592A.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33DCBBF7E53FFDFFF3F75DADC29F872" pageId="33" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
